
## 1. Pseudo-class selectors
pseudo-class is a keyword added to a selector that specifies a special state of the selected element(s). For example, :hover

The syntax of pseudo-classes:
```
selector:pseudo-class {
  property: value;
}
```

Example
```
/* unvisited link */
a:link {
  color: #FF0000;
}

/* visited link */
a:visited {
  color: #00FF00;
}

/* mouse over link */
a:hover {
  color: #FF00FF;
}

/* selected link */
a:active {
  color: #0000FF;
}
```
